            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>S. W. cor. Seventh &#38; &#91;&#63;&#93; Streets.<lb/>
                Philadelphia March 15. 1878.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir&#58;&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>We are in receipt just<lb/> this moment of a letter from Dr.<lb/> De Sola&#44; in which he requests<lb/> us to send you the titles of<lb/> Vol I&#44; and some proof sheets<lb/> of Vol 5&#44; also the title of Vol 5<lb/></p>
            <p>All the above matter has<lb/> already been sent to Dr. De<lb/> Sola&#44; consequently there<lb/> will be no occasion to trouble<lb/> you with it&#44; besides having been<lb/> already sent to him&#44; we<lb/> of course cannot send it to you<lb/></p>
            <p>The only exception to the<lb/> above is Vol 5 which we will<lb/> mail tonight<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours truly<lb/>
                							Sherman &#38; Co<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                No 546 North 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Street.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
